<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<!--@import "_head.kit"-->

<body>
    <!--@import "_header.kit"-->

    <main>
        <section class="hero section-fade">
            <div class="container hero-grid">
                <div class="hero-copy">
                    <p class="eyebrow">Portfolio / Digital Design / Product Management </p>
                    <h1>product designer who connects business, data, and design to create better customer experiences
                    </h1>
                    <p class="lead">I optimize digital journeys by combining strategic thinking, user research, and
                        data-driven decisions. From São Paulo to Lisbon, I've worked on products that balance user needs
                        with business impact.
                    </p>
                    <div class="button-row">
                        <a href="/portfolio.html" class="btn btn-primary">view selected work</a>
                        <a href="/contact.html" class="btn btn-secondary">about me</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="hero-card" aria-label="Abstract portfolio preview">
                    <div class="orbit orbit-one"></div>
                    <div class="orbit orbit-two"></div>
                    <div class="preview-panel">
                        <span>Selected Work</span>
                        <strong>04</strong>
                    </div>
                    <div class="preview-stack">
                        <span></span>
                        <span></span>
                        <span></span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="intro-section">
            <div class="container split-section">
                <div>
                    <p class="eyebrow">Introduction</p>
                    <h2>A generalist profile shaped by business, design and technology.</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="intro-copy">
                    <p>I started from a business and financial background, working with product teams, commercial areas
                        and operational journeys in fintech and banking environments. Over time, I became increasingly
                        interested in how digital products are experienced by people. Not only how they perform as
                        business assets.</p>
                    <p>Today, my work sits at the intersection of Product Strategy, Digital Experience Design and
                        Business Analysis. I use journey mapping, funnel analysis, research and stakeholder
                        collaboration to identify friction points, improve decision-making and design experiences that
                        are clearer, faster and more useful.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="featured-section">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="section-heading">
                    <p class="eyebrow">Featured Projects</p>
                    <h2>Recent work</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="project-grid">
                    <article class="project-card">
                        <a href="/project-1.html" class="project-cover" aria-label="Open Project One">
                            <img src="/assets/images/projects/mova-hero@1x.jpg" srcset="/assets/images/projects/mova-hero@1x.jpg 1x, /assets/images/projects/mova-hero@2x.jpg 2x" width="1200" height="750" alt="Placeholder image for the MOVA assisted sales journey case study" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                        </a>
                        <div class="project-card-body">
                            <p class="project-meta">Product Strategy / 2024</p>
                            <h3><a href="/project-1.html">MOVA — Assisted Sales Journey Optimization</a></h3>
                            <p>The project focused on simplifying a installment financing flow while balancing
                                operational efficiency, customer clarity and business compliance.</p>
                        </div>
                    </article>
                    <article class="project-card">
                        <a href="/project-2.html" class="project-cover" aria-label="Open Project Two">
                            <img src="/assets/images/projects/eventbrite-wallet-hero@1x.jpg" srcset="/assets/images/projects/eventbrite-wallet-hero@1x.jpg 1x, /assets/images/projects/eventbrite-wallet-hero@2x.jpg 2x" width="1200" height="750" alt="Placeholder image for the Eventbrite Wallet case study" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                        </a>
                        <div class="project-card-body">
                            <p class="project-meta">Service Design / 2026</p>
                            <h3><a href="/project-2.html">Eventbrite Wallet — Reducing Queues and Unlocking In-Event
                                    Revenue</a></h3>
                            <p>A digital wallet concept inside the Eventbrite app that allows attendees to buy food,
                                drinks and event services before or during an event, then redeem them quickly through a
                                QR-based flow.</p>
                        </div>
                    </article>
                </div>
                <div class="section-action">
                    <a href="/portfolio.html" class="text-link">See all projects</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <!--@import "_footer.kit"-->
</body>

</html>

